modules.description: Provides compression and decompression routines using the LZO algorithm, operating on byte sequences and input/output buffers. Supports streaming operations for efficient handling of large data sets. Enables real-time data reduction in network transmission and storage scenarios.

Calculates Adler-32 checksums for substrings using a base offset and length, and performs in-place compression and decompression of string data with explicit control over input and output ranges. Operates on raw strings, allowing direct manipulation of byte sequences without additional encoding. Used to efficiently compress log data before storage and decompress it during retrieval, ensuring minimal overhead for streaming applications.
